# login
Command:        login - log into the computer
Syntax:         login [user]
Flags:          (none)
Examples:       login ast               # Login as ast

     Login allows a logged in user to login as someone else without first 
logging out.  If a password is needed, login will prompt for it.  Login will
time out after 30 seconds, and will delay after a bad username is entered.
It will not allow login if /etc/nologin exists.  If /usr/adm/wtmp exists init
and login will use it for accounting purposes.  (It will also be used by other
programs such as write). If this file does not exist, neither init nor login
will create it.  Note that if you decide to create an empty /usr/adm/wtmp to
enable login accounting, it will grow forever and eventually fill up your disk
unless you manually truncate it from time to time.

